You can simply ask Alexa to control the contacts of your Jellyfish or ask information's about temperature and humidity to your NeoLighter. You need for this a PLH Jelyfish, a PLH NeoLighter, a wifi 2,4Ghz system and an Alexa Echo and Alexa App
Connect Alexa to your products in a few simple steps:

(1). Configure PLH devices following the specific instructions
(2). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market then configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(3). Search “PLH Jellyfish” skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(5). Enable “PLH Jellyfish” skill, and you'll be navigated to “PLH Jellyfish” login page;
(6). Follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(7). Now all setup is finished. You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the output 1”
“Alexa, turn off the output 2”
